<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1440,1184,1402]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,323,1184,1208]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Noguera, 1993" authorityName="Noguera" authorityYear="1993" box="[332,787,1184,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncideres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paurosoma">
<emphasis box="[332,598,1184,1208]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oncideres paurosoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Noguera, F. A." box="[606,787,1185,1209]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="9 - 60" refId="ref4594" refString="Noguera, F. A. 1993. Revision taxonomica del genero Oncideres Serville en Mexico (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). Folia Entomologica Mexicana 88: 9 - 60." type="journal article" year="1993">Noguera, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from four specimens (one male, three females) from 
<collectingRegion box="[366,478,1217,1241]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[538,632,1217,1241]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[643,733,1217,1241]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1885" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1885" box="[743,1099,1216,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Taricanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[743,949,1217,1240]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Taricanus minor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bates, H. W." box="[956,1099,1216,1240]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="249 - 436" refId="ref4231" refString="Bates, H. W. 1885. Supplement to Longicornia. Biologia Centrali-Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera 5: 249 - 436." type="journal article" year="1885">Bates, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a series of specimens collected in Jalapa (
<collectingRegion box="[598,713,1249,1273]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[734,824,1249,1273]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dillon, L. S. &amp; E. S. Dillon" box="[835,1130,1249,1273]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 186" refId="ref4255" refString="Dillon, L. S., and E. S. Dillon. 1945. The tribe Onciderini (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). Part I. Reading, Scientific Publications, Reading Public Museum and Art Gallery 5: 1 - 186." type="journal article" year="1945">Dillon and Dillon (1945)</bibRefCitation>
later proposed the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dillon &amp; Dillon" authorityYear="1945" box="[192,334,1281,1304]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Microcanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,334,1281,1304]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Microcanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for this latter species. Examination of the female 
<typeStatus box="[946,1056,1281,1305]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">lectotype</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1885" box="[1214,1327,1281,1304]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Taricanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[1214,1327,1281,1304]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">M. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(BMNH) and a female 
<typeStatus box="[359,468,1314,1338]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">paratype</typeStatus>
specimen (ACMT) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Noguera" authorityYear="1993" box="[736,908,1313,1336]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncideres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paurosoma">
<emphasis box="[736,908,1313,1336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">O. paurosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed no characters to separate the two species (
<figureCitation box="[290,357,1345,1369]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[192,275,1587,1609]" captionTargetBox="[369,1329,213,1553]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[369,1329,213,1553]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Four species of Onciderini. a) Microcanus minor (Bates, 1885), lectotype female, close-up of pronotum and elytral humeri. b) Oncideres paurosoma Noguera, 1993, paratype female, close-up of pronotum and elytral humeri. c) Microcanus minor (Bates, 1885), lectotype female, close-up of head. d) Oncideres paurosoma Noguera, 1993, paratype female, close-up of head. e) Oncioderes rondoniae Martins and Galileo, 1990, holotype female. f) Oncioderes piauiensis Martins and Galileo, 2013, holotype female. g) Oncioderes piauiensis Martins and Galileo, 2013, holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3673218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3673218/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
aâ€“d). Based on the absence of morphological features to separate the two species and similar distribution, 
<taxonomicName authority="Noguera, 1993" authorityName="Noguera" authorityYear="1993" box="[346,782,1377,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oncideres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paurosoma">
<emphasis box="[346,603,1377,1401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Oncideres paurosoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Noguera, F. A." box="[608,782,1378,1402]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="9 - 60" refId="ref4594" refString="Noguera, F. A. 1993. Revision taxonomica del genero Oncideres Serville en Mexico (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). Folia Entomologica Mexicana 88: 9 - 60." type="journal article" year="1993">Noguera, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,990,1377,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">synonymized</emphasis>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1055,1436,1377,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Microcanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[1055,1271,1378,1401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Microcanus minor</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bates, H. W." box="[1285,1427,1377,1402]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="249 - 436" refId="ref4231" refString="Bates, H. W. 1885. Supplement to Longicornia. Biologia Centrali-Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera 5: 249 - 436." type="journal article" year="1885">Bates, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
